"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48185","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-04-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) regularly consults with the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and other Government Departments and intelligence agencies, as well as our allies and partners, constantly to review or identify potential threats to UK Overseas Territories (UKOTs). In the first instance the MOD seeks to deter such attacks using deterrence measures including, where necessary, permanently based military garrisons or dedicated patrols, visits by deployed military forces, and more broadly the maintenance of world class deployable military forces. Should deterrence fail to prevent an attack, the Department remains confident that it has the necessary contingency plans and high readiness deployable forces in the UK and elsewhere to respond accordingly to any attack on a UKOT.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48185/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48185/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of readiness to defend its Overseas Territories in the event of attack.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","196321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48186","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-05-06","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48186/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48186/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what levels of stock his Office holds of (a) stationery, (b) printer cartridges, (c) treasury tags and other fasteners and (d) other office consumables.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","Mr John Redwood","196202"
