"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48305","House of Commons Commission","false","2014-04-30","<p>The House purchases stationery, printer cartridges, fasteners and other consumable items through a contract providing a next day delivery service. No central stocks are held.</p>","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","John Thurso",,"2014-04-30T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48305/answer","Biography information for Viscount Thurso","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48305/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48305/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross representing the House of Commons Commission, what levels of stock the House of Commons Commission holds of (a) stationery, (b) printer cartridges, (c) treasury tags and other fasteners and (d) other office consumables.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","Mr John Redwood","196210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48306","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>DFID does not hold information on stock levels. Stationery and other items, including printer cartridges, are ordered and distributed as and when required.</p><p> </p>","Rutland and Melton","Mr Alan Duncan",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48306/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48306/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48306/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what levels of stock her Department holds of (a) stationery, (b) printer cartridges, (c) treasury tags and other fasteners and (d) other office consumables.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","Mr John Redwood","196211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48307","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-28","<p>The UK has committed a total of £600m to the New Alliance for Food, Security and Nutrition. This includes £480m in funding commitments made through Country Cooperation Frameworks; a £76m contribution to the Global Agriculture and Food Security Programme and a further £44m for enabling actions. The New Alliance was launched in May 2012 and the full £600m will be spent by the end of 2018.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48307/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48307/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48307/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much support her Department is giving to the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","196345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48308","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-28","<p>Every DFID programme which is contributing to the New Alliance initiative is subject to DFID's annual review processes. In addition, this year, partner governments will conduct their first annual reviews of the effects of the New Alliance at country level.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48308/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48308/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48308/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how her Department measures the effect of support for the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","196346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48309","Department for International Development","false","2014-04-28","<p>DFID funding to New Alliance programmes is not disaggregated in the form requested, though much of the expenditure committed by DFID under the New Alliance includes programmes which specifically targets smallholder farmers.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48309/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48309/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48309/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department gives to small-scale food producers in areas supported by the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","196347"
