"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48326","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice does not use calculations of (a) the value of preventing a fatality, (b) willingness to pay and (c) cost-per-quality adjusted life year approach to quantify the value of a policy intervention.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice uses a range of analytical approaches to assess and evaluate policies, including quantifying the benefits, in line with guidance provided by HM Treasury:</p><ul><li>“The Green Book: appraisal and evaluation in central government”</li><li>“The Magenta Book” on designing an evaluation.</li></ul><p> </p><p>These are published on the HM Treasury website:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-green-book-appraisal-and-evaluation-in-central-governent" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-green-book-appraisal-and-evaluation-in-central-governent</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-magenta-book" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-magenta-book</a></p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48326/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48326/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, in what circumstances he uses a calculation of the (a) value of preventing a fatality, (b) willingness to pay and (c) cost-per-quality adjusted life year approach to quantify the value of a policy intervention; what other tools he uses to quantify the benefit of a policy intervention; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen O'Brien","Eddisbury","Mr Stephen O'Brien","196466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48327","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-29","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of offenders found guilty of offences under Sections 127 and 128 of the Mental Health Act 1983 in England and Wales, from 2008 to 2012 (latest data available) can be viewed in the table. There have been no findings of guilt recorded under Section 129 in this time period.</p><p> </p><p>Court proceedings data for 2013 are planned for publication in May 2014</p><p> </p><p>Data for offences under Section 126 of the Mental Health Act 1983 cannot be separately analysed from other offences under other statutes. This information is held by the individual courts in England and Wales but could only be separately identified at disproportionate cost</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-04-29T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48327/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48327/answer","196450 (table).xls","196450 (table).xls","Table 1","Table 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48327/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been convicted of an offence contrary to sections 126 to 129 of the Mental Health Act 1983 in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","196450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48328","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Murder, infanticide and kidnapping are all indictable only offences. A life sentence is mandatory for murder and the maximum penalty for infanticide and kidnapping.</p><p> </p><p>The number of offenders found guilty at all courts of 'murder', 'infanticide' and 'kidnapping' in England and Wales from 2009 to 2012 (latest data available) can be viewed in the table.</p><p> </p><p>Court proceedings data for 2013 is planned for publication in May 2014.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Ashford","Damian Green","196437","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48328/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48328/answer","Copy of PQ 196437 196451 table.xls","Copy of PQ 196437 196451 table.xls","Table 1","Table 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48328/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been convicted of an offence contrary to Section 1 of the Infanticide Act 1938 in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","196451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48329","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>Court proceedings data for 2013 are planned for publication in May 2014.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48329/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48329/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prosecutions under the Hunting Act 2004 there were in 2013; how many of those prosecutions were successful; and what offences these prosecutions involved.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","196479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48330","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-12","<p> </p><p> </p><p>We expect the review of spend on judges' lodgings to conclude before the summer.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-05-12T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48330/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48330/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 30 January 2014, Official Report, columns 649-50W on judges: housing, when he expects the review of the spend on judges' lodging to be completed.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","Mr John Spellar","196453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48331","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The training to deliver the Ibaana programme has just been completed. Prisoners will be offered the programme in the coming months.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48331/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48331/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners in each prison have (a) started and (b) completed the Ibaana programme since it was introduced.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","196380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48332","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>The investigation into Mr Mire's conduct was initiated by the President of the Residential Property Tribunal in accordance with the Judicial Complaints (Tribunals) Rules 2008 and the Judicial Discipline (Prescribed Procedures) Regulations 2006 (as amended). The Judicial Conduct Investigations Office was advised of the complaint against Mr Mire on the 13 October 2011.</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The investigation was conducted in accordance with the Regulations and ceased upon Mr Mire's resignation as a Valuer Chair of the Southern Property Tribunal on the 16 July 2013.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48332/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48332/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when the Judicial Conduct Investigations Office (a) started and concluded its investigation into Benjamin Mire; and what steps that Office subsequently took.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","196400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48334","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>The investigation into Mr Mire's conduct was conducted in accordance with the Judicial Discipline (Prescribed Procedures) Regulations (2006) (as amended). The Regulations require a draft of a review body report to be disclosed to the subject of the disciplinary process. The regulations were followed accordingly in this case.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48334/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48334/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether Benjamin Mire was shown the report of the Judicial Conduct Investigations Office into his conduct.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","196401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48335","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>Information gathered in the course of a judicial conduct investigation is confidential and may only be disclosed in the circumstances set out in section 139 of the Constitutional Reform Act 2005.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48335/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48335/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, under what circumstances the Judicial Conduct Investigations Office report on Benjamin Mire can be made public.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","196402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48337","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Mr Mire's conduct was investigated in accordance with The Judicial Discipline (Prescribed Procedures) Regulations 2006 (as amended). These regulations provide opportunities for the subject of the disciplinary process to make further representations and for the Lord Chancellor and the Lord Chief Justice to consider these and take such action as they think fit. It is therefore not possible to specify a time frame for concluding the disciplinary process. Mr Mire resigned before the disciplinary process was concluded.</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Since 1st October 2013, judicial conduct has been considered under the Judicial Discipline (Prescribed Procedures) Regulations 2013. These now provide for the Lord Chancellor and Lord Chief Justice to continue to make a finding of misconduct in certain circumstances where a judicial office holder has ceased to hold office during the course of a conduct investigation.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48337/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48337/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what timescale Benjamin Mire would have been removed from his appointment to the property tribunal following the conclusion of the report on the Judicial Conduct Investigations Office had he not resigned from that post.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","196403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48338","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p> </p><p>We are aware of two security breaches within the Prison Information Technology Academies (PICTA) since 1 January 2014. These came to the attention of Ministers on 26 February 2014. As a precaution we immediately suspended the use of the PICTA workshops across the prison estate, pending an investigation which is still in progress. It would therefore not be appropriate to comment further at this stage. In addition we are increasing the security measures within PICTA workshops and we expect them to re-open in the near future.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48338/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48338/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what security breaches associated with the Prisons ICT Academy programme there have been since 1 January 2014; when these first came to the attention of Ministers; what the (a) nature of and (b) the outcome of their investigation was; and what illegal activities by prisoners were uncovered.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","196383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48339","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-06","<p> </p><p>Final bids to run the Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are expected in June 2014, and will be rigorously assessed against robust quality, legal, commercial and financial criteria. In the Pre-Qualification Questionnaire, bidders were required to declare that they had no convictions in relation to criminal offences such as conspiracy, corruption, bribery, fraud or criminal offences relating to the conduct of their business or profession and acts of grave misconduct. The MoJ also undertook extensive due diligence of bidders on a range of matters, including integrity and legal compliance issues. As a consequence we have a robust and diverse market and are confident that the bidders who passed the first stage of the competition – the Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (PQQ) - are credible organisations.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48339/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48339/answer","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48339/answer/previousversion/7640","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what rules his Department has in place on the (a) proven and (b) alleged criminal actions of potential bidders for the Transforming Rehabilitaiton programme.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","196384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48340","Home Office","false","2014-04-29","<p> </p><p>The requested information is not held centrally. The Home Office holds data on <br>offences recorded by the police.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-04-29T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48340/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48340/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many cases of (a) domestic and (b) sexual abuse were reported by victims attending a police station in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","196377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48341","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-28","<p> </p><p>Mr Mire's chose to resign as a Valuer Chair of the Southern Property Tribunal on the 16 July 2013 following an investigation into his conduct. The reasons given by Mr Mire form part of the information gathered in the course of a judicial conduct investigation which is confidential and may only be disclosed in certain circumstances as set out in section 139 of the Constitutional Reform Act 2005.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-04-28T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48341/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48341/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when and for what reasons Benjamin Mire left his judicial appointment on the property tribunal.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","196399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48342","Home Office","false","2014-04-29","<p> </p><p>The requested information is not held centrally. The Home Office holds data on <br>offences recorded by the police.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-04-29T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48342/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48342/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the (a) number and (b) proportion of crimes reported in a police station in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","196378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48344","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-14","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of offenders found guilty at all courts of the offences specified in the Sexual Offences Act 2003, the Sexual Offences (Amendment) Act 2000, the Indecency with Children Act 1960, the Sexual Offences Act 1967 and the Criminal Law Act 1977, in England and Wales, from 2008 to 2012 is provided in the attached tables.</p><p> </p><p>Please note that offences under the Sexual Offences Act 2003 sections 9 to 12, 14 to 19, 25 to 26, 47 to 50 provide data where the victim can be specifically identified as a child, whereas offences under sections 3, 4, 52 to 53, 57 to 59, 61 and 66 to 67, are not specific to the age of the victim.</p><p> </p><p>The tables do not include data for offences under section 5 of the Sexual Offences Act 1967, or under section 3 of the Sexual Offences (Amendment) Act 2000. These offences, along with section 54 of the Criminal Law Act 1977, were repealed by the Sexual Offences Act 2003 and there have been no convictions in the last four years.</p><p> </p><p>The number of offenders found guilty of offences under section 2 of the Sexual Offences Act 2003 was provided in answer to PQ 193582 and can be found at<em> Official Report </em>c638W, 1 April 2014. It is not possible to separate out the age of the victims of offences under section 2.</p><p> </p><p>Similarly, it is not possible to separate out the age of the victim of offences committed under sections 30 – 41 Sexual Offences Act 2003 from centrally held data. For data on offences under this legislation as a whole, I refer the honourable lady to the answer provided to PQ 193810, which can be found at <em>Official Report </em> column 136W, 7 April 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Section 20 of the Sexual Offences Act 2003 deals with offences in Scotland and Northern Ireland. Statistics for these offences in Scotland are a matter for the Scottish Government, with those in Northern Ireland being a matter for the Department of Justice Northern Ireland</p><p> </p><p>Court proceedings data for England and Wales for 2013 are planned for publication in May 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The Government takes very seriously all matters relating to the sexual abuse of children and adults. Our laws in these areas are rightly robust and clear. The 2003 Act, which came into effect in May 2004, significantly modernised and strengthened the laws on sexual offences in England and Wales.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","196329 ; 196330 ; 196331 ; 196332 ; 196438 ; 196439 ; 196443","2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48344/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48344/answer","Table 1&2.xls ; Tables 3&4.xls ; table 5.xls","Table 1&2.xls ; Tables 3&4.xls ; table 5.xls","Table 1 ; Table 2 ; Table 3","Table 1 ; Table 2 ; Table 3","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48344/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been convicted of an offence contrary to section 1 of the Indecency with Children Act 1960 in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","196436"
